introduction.title: Introduction
introduction.desc: Learn about Latent Box's philosophy, vision, and mission
introduction.p1: Latent Box is a reinvented resource site, maintained by Latent Cat. Why are we doing this? We have a few pursuits:
introduction.p2: Bridging the information gap with high-quality content.
introduction.p3: We don't need another search engine, a massive collection of websites and products, or complex automation, retrieval, and user systems - because no one will look at those. We hope that when we curate a thousand sites, a hundred of them will be genuinely good things that users will open, try, and remember.
introduction.p4: Promoting diversity and interdisciplinary collaboration as much as possible.
introduction.p5: We believe that a good product, good technology, and a good team involve a broad range of disciplinary knowledge and professional skills. We hope that this collection can cover as many creative fields as possible. Therefore, it is suitable for those who are equally enthusiastic about breaking through themselves.
introduction.p6: Maintaining updates and engaging in community co-creation.
introduction.p7: Keeping updates is challenging, and the community will be our motivation to persist. Therefore, we have open-sourced the entire website on GitHub and established Twitter and Xiaohongshu accounts, as well as Discord and WeChat groups. You can share content with us on any platform and directly submit pull requests on GitHub, add contributor names. Besides, your every 'like' will be our greatest encouragement.
introduction.p8: This is the original intention of setting up Latent Box, and we hope to bring some help to everyone!

follow-us.title: Follow Us
follow-us.desc: Follow our latest updates on social media platforms
follow-us.p1: It is not easy to maintain the website. If you want to know our latest updates, please follow our social accounts! We will release the latest collections and product recommendations as soon as possible, and we look forward to your feedback!

diffuseum.title: Diffuseum Podcast
diffuseum.desc: Diffuseum is a community interested in generative images and open-source AI. This podcast documents stories of frontline developers we follow.

ep1.title: How a Gen-Z's Homework Made AI Image Generation 10x Faster
ep1.content:
Gen-Z AI researcher Allen's coursework LCM accelerated Stable Diffusion inference by 10x, bringing AI image generation into real-time inference, which has garnered millions of downloads and applications in the open-source community.

In addition to sharing this young researcher's background and community stories, this episode also raises an open perspective: the 'real-time' nature of generation constitutes a qualitative change in AI interaction experience for C-end users, thus containing excellent product opportunities.

So, which forms of applications will be transformed? We look forward to brainstorming with listeners, and welcome any ideas.

ep2.title: Dialogue with InstantID: My Face, AI's Relentless Battlefield
ep2.content:
Just upload a photo, and without waiting, my face instantly enters the multiverse. With the emergence of the open-source tool InstantID, AI portraits have reached new heights - a face can appear in real-time in any scene described by prompts, even LeCun couldn't resist sharing and interacting. Looking back at the past year, portraits have been one of the few successful productization directions in the AI field. No matter how technology evolves, it seems we still care about our faces first.

In addition to focusing on the story behind InstantID's young developers, this episode also raises questions: Is the product potential of AI portraits not yet fully tapped? What elements drive these algorithm teams to compete? We look forward to brainstorming with listeners and welcome any thoughts.
